285 g Shrimp
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
227 g Broccoli
1 unit(s) Lemon
¾ cup Basmati Rice
1 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add rice and broth concentrate to the boiling water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Line a baking sheet with foil.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp. Pat shrimp dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and mayo to a medium bowl, toss to coat.
Add panko to bowl, then toss to coat each shrimp.
Shake off any excess breading, then arrange coated shrimp on prepared sheet.

Roast in the top of the oven until crust is golden and shrimp is cooked through, 8-10min. **

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then broccoli and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender, 4-5 min.
Meanwhile, zest, then juice half the lemon (use whole lemon for 4 ppl). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.
Thinly slice green onions.

Add lemon zest, garlic spread and lemon juice to a small microwaveable bowl. Stir to combine. Microwave on high for 10-20 seconds until garlic spread has melted.
Fluff rice with a fork. Stir in green onions and season with salt.
Divide rice between plates. Top with broccoli and shrimp.
Drizzle lemon-garlic butter over shrimp and broccoli.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.

If you've opted to get shrimp, line another baking sheet with foil. Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp. Pat dry with paper towels. Add shrimp and mayo to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Add panko to the same bowl, then toss to coat each shrimp. Shake off any excess breading, then arrange shrimp in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet.

Roast shrimp the way the recipe instructs you to roast the tilapia.